{
  "texts": [
    "Here, we discuss some of the most important techniques employed so far, in particular readout error mitigation, zero noise extrapolation and optimized circuit compilation.",
    "Depending on the hardware, other mitigation techniques can be more important that those discussed here, but the principal theme of these approaches remains the same.",
    "Readout error mitigation is a technique used to correct for errors that occur during the measuring process.",
    "By performing multiple measurements of the same qubit state it is possible to use a statistical method to suppress readout errors.",
    "This can be done by measuring the qubit in multiple bases and using a maximum likelihood estimation algorithm to infer the true state."
  ]
}